CULLIFORD V. GADD. (Superior Court of New York City,

General Term.

March 14, 1892.) Motion for reargument. ■ Motion denied. For decision on appeal, see 17 N. Y. Supp. 457.

Argued before Dugro and Gildersleeve, JJ.

Sidney Harris, for appellant. F. Speigelberg, for respondent. Per Curiam.

The general term passed upon the facts disclosed in the case in the way that they would have passed upon them if there had been a .statement that the case contained all the evidence. Motion denied, with $10 costs.
